Description: The about:blank URI references a blank page.

The about:invalid URI references a non-existent
        document with a generic error condition. It can be used when a URI is
        necessary, but the default value shouldn't be resolveable as any type
        of document.
Used as the document's address of iframe srcdoc documents in HTML.
For use in DOCTYPEs in HTML documents when needed for compatibility with XML tools.
